This paper discusses the impact of password dataset distribution on guessing, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper explores the usability and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) aspects of password guessing. The paper also touches upon the topic of cybersecurity (cs.CY) and machine learning (cs.LG) in terms of proposing a function to measure the ability of one distribution to estimate another. Finally, the paper discusses the empirical analysis of password datasets, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
